result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan Lee Peterson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Nathan Lee Peterson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Nathan Lee Peterson was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Nathan Lee Peterson was found guilty of Possess Amphetamine/LSD/Psilocin, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(d).

records.addlTxt:
11:02 am - Defendant Nathan Lee Peterson appeared with attorney James Richard Lex.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DA states agreement. DE pleads NO CONTEST to Cts. 2 & 4.   Court questions DE regarding the plea.  DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC on Cts. 2 & 4 and on motion of DA dismisses Cts. 1 & 3. Comments by parties. Exam by Court. Comments and ruling by Court. Submit DNA sample. Appeal rights given. Adj. 11:24 am. 

Court imposes:
Ct. 2 - Sentence withheld - 18 months probation. Conditions: $243 court costs; $200 DNAAS; AODA; Obtain HSED or it's equivalent; Obtain and maintain full-time employment authorizing agent to relax condition if enrolled in full-time course of higher education; Eligible to apply for expungement
Ct. 4 - Sentence withheld - 18 months probation. Conditions: $243 court costs; AODA; Obtain HSED or it's equivalent; Obtain and maintain full-time employment authorizing agent to relax condition if enrolled in full-time course of higher education; Eligible to apply for expungement
Disposal of contraband evidence after appeal time limits have expired.
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 26, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Nathan Lee Peterson appeared with attorney James Richard Lex.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint acknowledged, reading waived.  Preliminary hearing requested, time limits waived.  Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled. Bond to continue.
State's Demand for Discovery & Notice of Intent to Use DNA Evidence
